canonical:
  title: 法壽齋疏
  author: 釋宓菴
  language: lzh
  text: 千重寶珠影裏聖乎凡乎一面古鏡光中師也弟也理雖無彼我之異事則有自他之殊宜歸佛兮無歸而歸乃祝師以不祝之祝惟曹溪老和尙是震旦大沙門一開爐鞴以接機幾許人天之賴福旣慈悲出現且隨凡俗以同塵故寒暑推移已涉春秋於環甲其在迷盲之念盍懷戰懼之情肆修同涓滴之功緣用薦等虛空之壽量兾眞誠之一片格妙鑒於十方伏願大和尙法臘增崇甲子周天而不老色身永固毗嵐偃嶽而恒寧
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 法壽齋疏
  author: 釋宓菴
  language: lzh
  text: 千重寶珠影裏。聖乎凡乎。一面古鏡光中。師也弟也。理雖無彼我之異。事則有自他之殊。宜歸佛兮無歸而歸。乃祝師以不祝之祝。惟曹溪老和尙。是震旦大沙門。一開爐鞴以接機。幾許人天之賴福。旣慈悲出現。且隨凡俗以同塵。故寒暑推移。已涉春秋於環甲。其在迷盲之念。盍懷戰懼之情。肆修同涓滴之功緣。用薦等虛空之壽量。兾眞誠之一片。格妙鑒於十方。伏願大和尙法臘增崇。甲子周天而不老。色身永固。毗嵐偃嶽而恒寧。
korean:
  title: 법수재 소
  author: 석복암
  language: kor
  text: 1천 겹으로 싸인 보주(寶珠)의 그림자 속에는 성인도 범부도 비추고, 한 면의 옛 거울의 광명 속에는 스승도 제자도 어립니다. 이치로는 저와 나의 다름이 없지마는 사상(事相)으로는 자기와 남의 다른 것이 있으므로, 부처님께 귀의하되, 귀의할 것이 없는데 귀의하며, 스승님을 축수하되, 축수할 것이 없을 때까지 축수합니다. 우리 조계의 노스님은 동방[震旦]의 큰 사문(沙門)이라, 한 번 화로와 풀무를 개설하여 여러 기류(機類)를 접대하시어, 얼마나 사람과 하늘의 복을 힘입으셨습니까. 이미 자비함을 나타내시고 또 세속을 좇아서 일을 같이 하시기에 세월이 흘러가서 춘추(春秋)가 벌써 환갑(還甲)이 되었으니, 이 어리석은 생각에 조심스럽고 송구한 정을 품지 않을 수 없습니다. 이에 물방울보다도 작은 공을 드려서 허공과 같이 무한한 수명을 축원하오니, 이 일편의 참된 정성이 시방 삼세[十方三世]의 부처님에 감응되소서. 엎드려 원합니다. 큰 스님께서 법랍(法臘)이 더 높으셔서 갑자(甲子)가 하늘을 두루하도록 늙지 마시고, 색신(色身)이 길이 강건하시어 격심한 바람이[毗嵐] 동산에 누우셔서 항상 편안하여지이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1150_010_0050&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 법수재 : '
    value: 원오국사(圓悟國師)를 위하여 재(齋)를 행함.
english:
  title: In Praise of the Dharma Longevity Ritual
  author: Seok Bok-am
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Within the shadow of the jewel wrapped in a thousand layers, both sage and ordinary being are reflected; in the light of the ancient mirror's single face, both master and disciple appear. In principle there is no distinction between self and other, yet in manifestation there exists a difference between oneself and another. Thus we return to the Buddha, though there is nothing to return to—we return nonetheless. We offer blessings to the Master, though there is nothing to bless—we bless until there is nothing left to bless.

    Our venerable patriarch of Caoxi is the great monk of the Eastern land. Opening once the forge and bellows of the dharma, he received the various types of beings, and how many among humans and celestials have relied upon his blessing! Already manifesting compassion, he joins the common dust of the secular world. Thus as seasons turn and pass, spring and autumn have already completed their cycle—sixty years round—and before such wisdom, who could not feel reverence and humble restraint? So we offer a merit as small as a single drop of water to invoke a lifespan vast as empty space. May this single-pointed sincerity touch the Buddha's subtle awareness throughout the ten directions. We humbly wish that our Great Master's dharma age may ever ascend, that the cycle of sixty years may revolve endlessly without aging, that his form remain ever vigorous and strong, and that even the fierce wind of destruction may find him like a mountain in eternal peace.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Caoxi (曹溪) refers to the lineage of the Sixth Patriarch Huineng, a foundational figure in Chan Buddhism.
  - key: ''
    value: This ritual was performed in honor of Yuanwu Guoshi (圓悟國師), a renowned Chan master.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'ancient mirror' and 'jewel in a thousand layers' are traditional Chan Buddhist metaphors for the nature of mind and reality.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'cycle of sixty years' (甲子) refers to the completion of the Chinese sexagenary cycle, marking a significant milestone in a person's life.
